Source: plproxy
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), flex, bison, libpq-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/plproxy/plproxy

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-plproxy
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-plproxy
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: database partitioning implemented as a PostgreSQL procedural language
 PL/Proxy is a PostgreSQL procedural language handler for remote procedure calls
 between PostgreSQL databases, with optional sharding.
